race.comment: LOTTA CITY (9) jumped out well and found one better at Pakenham on debut. Has upside, and this is a touch easier. Strips fitter and she can go one better. GREAT FUEGO (7) missed a whisker at Kyneton over 1400m, making sharp improvement. Comes back to the shorter sprint freshened and has been kept up to the mark with a winning jumpout. Draws out, but expect the Hayes-trained galloper to finish hard. CHAMPAGNE EXPRESS (5) resumes and was nudged out at Sandown-Lakeside at her only fresh outing. Went close there before the spell, and her jumpouts suggest she's right on song. SWEET FARNAN (12) did a good job for a resuming second and can progress off that.
